<h3 id="theorem-1">Theorem 1</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Let A,B and C be Matrices of the same size, and let r and s be scalar.
    <ul>
      <li>
\[A+B=B+A\]
      </li>
      <li>
\[(A+B)+C=A+(B+C)\]
      </li>
      <li>
\[A+0=A\]
      </li>
      <li>
\[r(A+B)=rA+rB\]
      </li>
      <li>
\[(r+s)A = rA+sA\]
      </li>
      <li>
\[r(sA)=(rs)A\]
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>ì¢Œìš°ì˜  matrix sizeê°€ ë™ì¼í•˜ë‹¤.</li>
</ul>

